name: Cook County Assessor's Residential Property Characteristics
description: Assessment dataset used by the Cook County Assessor in their Computer Assisted Mass Appraisal (CAMA) system used to assess residential properties in Northern Triennial Townships. This dataset contains property information for every residential PIN in the northern triennial townships where class is within a specified list of classes. For disclaimers, see dataset narrative at https://datacatalog.cookcountyil.gov/stories/s/p2kt-hk36

submitter.displayName: Cook County Assessor's Office Data & Modeling Department

columns.name: PIN
columns.description: Unique Permanent Identification Number for each property. All PINs are 14 digits: 2 digits for area + 2 digits for sub area + 2 digits for block + 2 digits for parcel + 4 digits for the multicode

columns.name: Property Class
columns.description: Property class. For a list of property classes, see https://www.cookcountyassessor.com/assets/forms/classcode.pdf

columns.name: Tax Year
columns.description: Tax year of sale. Tax year referrs to the year in which taxes due. Taxes are billed a year in arrears. If a sale ocurred in calendar year 2018, it will be in tax year 2019.

columns.name: Neighborhood Code
columns.description: Neighborhood code as assigned by the Assessment office. An interactive map is available at https://maps.cookcountyil.gov/cookviewer/

columns.name: Land Square Feet
columns.description: Square feet of the land (not just the building) of the property. Note that land is divided into 'plots' and 'parcels' - this field applies to parcels, identified by PIN

columns.name: Town Code
columns.description: Township code as assigned by the Assessment office. An interactive map is available at https://maps.cookcountyil.gov/cookviewer/

columns.name: Type of Residence
columns.description: Type of residence - 1 = one story, 2 = two-story, 3 = three-story or higher, 4 = split level, 5 = 1.5 story, 6 = 1.6 story, 7 = 1.7 story , 8 = 1.8 story , 9 =  1.9 story (Note: residences with 1.5 - 1.9 stories are one story and have partial livable attics and are classified based on the square footage of the attic compared to the first floor of the house. So, 1.5 story houses have an attic that is 50% of the area of the first floor, 1.6 story houses are 60%, 1.7 are 70%, etc. However, what is recorded on the field card differs from what is in the database. All 1.5 - 1.9 story houses are coded as 5)

columns.name: Apartments
columns.description: Number of apartments in the building - 2 = Two,  3 = Three, 4 = Four, 5 = Five, 6 = Six, 0 = None

columns.name: Wall Material
columns.description: Exterior wall material - 1=Wood, 2=Masonry, 3=Wood&Masonry, 4=Stucco

columns.name: Roof Material
columns.description: Roof construction material. 1 = Shingle/Asphalt, 2 = Tar & Gravel, 3 = Slate, 4 = Shake, 5 = Tile, 6 = Other

columns.name: Rooms
columns.description: Number of rooms in the property (excluding baths). Not to be confused with bedrooms.

columns.name: Bedrooms
columns.description: Number of bedrooms in the property, defined based on building squarefoot and the judgement of the person in the field.

columns.name: Basement
columns.description: Basement type - 1 = Full, 2 = Slab, 3 = Partial, 4 = Crawl

columns.name: Basement Finish
columns.description: Basement finish -  1 = Formal rec room; 2 = Apartment; 3 = Unfinished

columns.name: Central Heating
columns.description: Central heating type  - 1 = Warm air, 2 = Hot water steam, 3 = Electric, 4 = Other

columns.name: Other Heating
columns.description: Other heating type - 1 = Floor furnace, 2 = Unit heater, 3 = Stove, 4 = Solar, 5 = none

columns.name: Central Air
columns.description: Is central airconditioning present? - 1 = yes, 2 = no

columns.name: Fireplaces
columns.description: Number of fireplaces, counted as the number of flues one can see from the outside of the building.

columns.name: Attic Type
columns.description: Type of attic - 1 = Full, 2 = partial, 3 = none

columns.name: Attic Finish
columns.description: Finish of attic - 1 = Living area, 2 = Apartment, 3 = unfinished

columns.name: Half Baths
columns.description: Number of half baths, defined as bathrooms without a shower or bathtub.

columns.name: Design Plan
columns.description: Plan of Design - 1 = architect, 2 = stock plan

columns.name: Cathedral Ceiling
columns.description: Cathedral Ceiling - 1 = yes, 2 = No. (Note: the column name comes from a variable that is no longer used, but the column name was not changed to reflect Cathedral Ceiling)

columns.name: Construction Quality
columns.description: Construction quality - 1 = Deluxe, 2 = Average, 3 = Poor (There is one 4 in this dataset, but no 3. In general, this column is not useful for analytical purposes)

columns.name: Renovation
columns.description: Construction renovation - 1 = yes, 2= no

columns.name: Site Desireability
columns.description: Site desireability - 1 = Beneficial to Value, 2 = Not relevant to Value, 3 = Detracts from Value. This field lack sufficient variation to be useful for modeling.

columns.name: Garage 1 Size
columns.description: Garage 1 size - 1 = 1 car, 2 = 1.5 car, 3 = 2 car, 4 = 2.5 cars, 5 = 3 cars, 6 = 3.5 cars, 7 = none, 8 = 4 cars

columns.name: Garage 1 Material
columns.description: Garage 1 construction -  1 = Frame, 2 = Masonry, 3= Frame/Masonry, 4 = Stucco

columns.name: Garage 1 Attachment
columns.description: Is Garage 1 attached? 1 = Yes, 2 = No

columns.name: Garage 1 Area
columns.description: Is Garage 1 physically including within the building area? 1 = Yes, 2 = No. If yes, the garage area is subtracted from the building square feet calculation by the field agent.

columns.name: Garage 2 Size
columns.description: Garage 2 size - 1 = 1 car, 2 = 1.5 car, 3 = 2 car, 4 = 2.5 cars, 5 = 3 cars, 6 = 3.5 cars, 7 = none, 8 = 4 cars

columns.name: Garage 2 Material
columns.description: Garage 2 construction -  1 = Frame, 2 = Masonry, 3= Frame/Masonry, 4 = Stucco

columns.name: Garage 2 Attachment
columns.description: Is Garage 2 attached? 1 = Yes, 2 = No

columns.name: Garage 2 Area
columns.description: Is Garage 2 physically including within the building area? 1 = Yes, 2 = No. If yes, the garage area is subtracted from the building square feet calculation by the field agent.

columns.name: Porch
columns.description: Enclosed porch - 1 = Frame, 2 = Masonry, 3 = None

columns.name: Other Improvements
columns.description: Other improvements - if not 0, they contain a code. The definitions of these codes are maintained by the field workers. Unfortunately, the way this data is entered makes it impossible to distinguish between a 1 & 2 and a 12, making this field mostly useless.

columns.name: Building Square Feet
columns.description: Building square feet, as measured from the exterior of the property

columns.name: Repair Condition
columns.description: State of Repair - 1 = Above average, 2 = Average, 3 = Below average

columns.name: Multi Code
columns.description: Variable that indicates that more one building exists on the PIN. 2 = one building, 3 = two buildings, etcâ€¦ through 7 = 6 buildings.

columns.name: Number of Commercial Units
columns.description: Number of commercial units (the vast majority are for properties with class 212).

columns.name: Prior Tax Year Market Value Estimate (Land)
columns.description: Board of Review final estimated market value of land from the prior tax year.

columns.name: Prior Tax Year Market Value Estimate (Building)
columns.description: Board of Review final estimated market value of building from the prior tax year.

columns.name: Date of Most Recent Sale
columns.description: Most recent date of sale, if a sale ocurred in the prior two years.

columns.name: Deed No.
columns.description: Deed number for sale

columns.name: Sale Price
columns.description: Most recent sale price, where available

columns.name: Longitude
columns.description: Longitude coordinate of the property's location, as defined by the centroid of the parcel shape in GIS.

columns.name: Latitude
columns.description: Latitude coordinate of the property's location, as defined by the centroid of the parcel shape in GIS.

columns.name: Census Tract
columns.description: Census tract identifier - full map available through the Census Bureau, https://www.census.gov/geo/maps-data/maps/2010ref/st17_tract.html

columns.name: Total Building Square Feet
columns.description: This field applies to condominium properties (299) only. It is the sum of interior square feet of all units in the building.

columns.name: Multi Property Indicator
columns.description: Indicator for a property with mutiple improvements on one PIN, e.g. a main house and a coach house. NOT to be confused with a property which was part of a multi-pin sale.

columns.name: Property Address
columns.description: Property street address, not the address of the taxpayer.

columns.name: Modeling Group
columns.description: Modeling group, as defined by the property class. Properties with class 200, 201, 241, 299 is defined as "NCHARS", short for "no characteristics", which are condos and vacant land classes.  Properties with class 202, 203, 204, 205, 206, 207, 208, 209, 210, 235, 278, and 295 are "SF", short for "single-family."  Properties with class 211 and 212 are "MF", short for ""multi-family."

columns.name: Full Baths
columns.description: Number of full bathrooms, defined as having a bath or shower. If this value is missing, the default value is set to 1.

columns.name: Age
columns.description: Age of the property. If missing, this defaults to 10. This field is a combination of original age and effective age where original age refers to the oldest component of the building and effective age is a relative judgement due to renovations or other improvements. For instance, if a property is completely demolished and built up again, the age resets to 1. But if portions of the original structure are kept, it may be more complicated to determine the age.

columns.name: Use
columns.description: Use of property - 1 = single family, 2 = multi-family. If absent, default value is 1.

columns.name: Number of Units
columns.description: For condos, the number of units in a building

columns.name: Percent Ownership
columns.description: Percent of ownership of a condo building for a unit as defined by the condominium declaration. If missing, default is 1/n_units.

columns.name: Condo Class Factor
columns.description: Factor variable for NCHARS modeling group. Divides  properties into two: Properties with class 200, 201, and 241 are given condo class factor as 200. Properties with class 299 are given condo class factor as 299

columns.name: Multi-Family Indicator
columns.description: Factor variable for MF modeling group. Properties with class 211 are given multi-family indicator as 211.  Properties with class 212 are given multi-family indicator as 212.

columns.name: Large Lot
columns.description: Large lot factor variable, where 1 acre of land (land square feet > 43559) is defined as a large lot. 1 = large lot, 0 = not a large lot.

columns.name: Condition, Desirability and Utility
columns.description: about 20 different codes attached to the face sheet that denote a number of seemingly unrelated characteristics associated with a PIN, ranging from condition to types of subsidies.  This field does not match across the SQL server/AS-400 for 2018.

columns.name: O'Hare Noise
columns.description: Indicator for the property under O'Hare approach flight path, within 1/4 mile.

columns.name: Floodplain
columns.description: Indicator for properties on a floodplain, defined as a FEMA Special Flood Hazard Area

columns.name: Near Major Road
columns.description: Indicates whether the property is within 300 ft of a major road.

columns.name: Total Units
columns.description: For condos, the number of both residential and non-residential units in a building

columns.name: Condo Strata
columns.description: For condominiums, shows the decile of mean unit market value a condominimum building is

columns.name: Age Squared
columns.description: Age Squared

columns.name: Age Decade
columns.description: Age in decades

columns.name: Age Decade Squared
columns.description: Age in decades squared

columns.name: Lot Size Squared
columns.description: Lot Size Squared

columns.name: Improvement Size Squared
columns.description: Building square feet, squared

columns.name: Location Factor
columns.description: Calculated from a geographically weighted regression. Captures the relationship between home value and geographic location.

columns.name: Garage indicator
columns.description: Indicates presence of a garage of any size.

columns.name: Residential share of building
columns.description: A sum of "percent of ownership" that only includes residential units within a condo building.

columns.name: Pure Market Sale
columns.description: Indicator for pure market sale

columns.name: Pure Market Filter
columns.description: Indicator for pure market sale

columns.name: Neigborhood Code (mapping)
columns.description: Unmodified neighborhood code that can be used for mapping.

columns.name: Square root of lot size
columns.description: Square root of lot size

columns.name: Square root of age
columns.description: Square root of age of improvement

columns.name: Square root of improvement size
columns.description: Square root of improvement size

columns.name: Town and Neighborhood
columns.description: Combination of town and neighborhood used to uniquely neighborhoods across townships.
